              Guide Details</font></b></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2">
              </td>
          </tr>

<tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><img border="0" src="../triangle.JPG"><font size="3" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>MISTY STORYSWAPPER</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Group / Solo:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Solo - Necromancer</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Mob Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">13 to 17</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Zone:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Karana, West</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Location:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Shop near Qeynos Hills (loc +850 -1900)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Character Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">12 to 16</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Strategy:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">I have hunted Misty now for far longer than I care to admit. When you are a level 12 hunting Misty, don't even think about casting fear or darkness. The thing to remember is that when she cons red, and you are a mighty bright green level 12, a failed darkness spell can basically screw you for the entire battle since heat blood gobbles up so much mana (and is indispensable). Even if darkness fails only 1 out of 3 times, that is one battle you stand a very good chance of losing. Also, fear is just a little too unstable for my taste. First, the spell has to take hold and then it has to take hold long enough to make any kind of difference. The few times fear actually worked on her, she took a few steps in panic before returning to me quickly with renewed fury.
<br><br>
When I was 12, I did the following. I walked out far enough so that I could cast spells on her. I then sent my pet even further back. I hit ole Misty with HB and then ran like hell passed my pet. I had the pet suitably distanced so that once she was really closing in on me, he stepped in and interrupted her pursuit. Even though pets may not be able to continually taunt a critter, the first attack always seems to work and further serves to slow critter down for a few more valuable seconds (heat blood!). I then fire off leach, poison, and weaken (!) one right after the other and close in to fight (very important note: I had a runed totem staff but with no armor to speak of).
<br><br>
I have no idea how much poison and weaken contributes, but I always use them (as a matter of good taste) and I never died to a red Misty at 12. My pet rarely died. It is certainly possibly I would have defeated her without them, but they are just too much fun to use. Also, weaken is a perfect timer for when she will spawn next. As soon as your stolen strength disappears, she pops up.
<br><br>
Once you get past 13 (and especially in the later levels), this bard is extremely easy. When I hit level 14, I used engulfing darkness as a pull, but it was more out of boredom than anything else.
<br><br>
One final point: I use strafing a lot in EQ. I have no idea how much difference this makes (if any at all), but I circle strafed Misty quite a bit which, combined with my pets attacks and taunts, seemed to freak her out a bit, making her constantly jump around and change directions. Again, this could have ZERO to do with my success with Misty, but you might want to experiment on your own.</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Author:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Gnuggalumpus (Bristlebane)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rating:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>7.4</b> (average of <b>5</b> votes)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rate this spot:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><FORM ACTION = "ratehg.asp" METHOD = post><SELECT NAME="Voting"><OPTION VALUE="0">Rate this Spot</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="1">1 - Don't even bother</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="2">2</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="3">3</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="4">4</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="5">5 - It is ok</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="6">6</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="7">7</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="8">8</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="9">9</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="10">10 - You must come here</OPTION></SELECT><INPUT TYPE = "hidden" NAME = "intHGID" VALUE 